# Thesis Progress Log
This journal tracks the experimental progress, observations, and iterative tuning of the swarm robotics simulation.

## Format
* **[TIMESTAMP]** YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM
* **[PHASE/TASK]** Briefly describe the current step in the roadmap or the experimental trial.
* **[OBSERVATION/RESULT]** Record what happened, focusing on stigmergy dynamics and physics behavior.
* **[NEXT STEP]** Actionable steps to fix bugs, tune parameters, or move to the next phase.

---

### Sample Entries

* **[TIMESTAMP]** 2026-06-03 14:00
* **[PHASE/TASK]** Baseline Testing - Mechanical Stigmergy on Convex Shapes (Circle, Square).
* **[OBSERVATION/RESULT]** Swarm sizes of 10 and 20 easily navigated the Circle through the gap. Square shape encountered slight rotational friction at the gap edges but successfully passed 80% of the time. Agents aligned naturally without explicit communication.
* **[NEXT STEP]** Proceed to test non-convex shapes (L-shape, C-shape) to see if pure mechanical pushing causes jamming at the gap.

* **[TIMESTAMP]** 2026-06-03 16:30
* **[PHASE/TASK]** Advanced Testing - Non-Convex Shapes (L-shape, C-shape).
* **[OBSERVATION/RESULT]** C-shape frequently hooked onto the edges of the gap, causing the swarm to continuously push into the wall. Mechanical stigmergy alone is insufficient to unhook the object; agents get trapped inside the C-cavity.
* **[NEXT STEP]** Introduce Vector Pheromones (Chemical Stigmergy) to allow agents stuck at the wall to broadcast repelling gradients, guiding the rest of the swarm to shift their pushing angle.

---

## Log Entries

* **[TIMESTAMP]** 2026-06-03 17:46
* **[PHASE/TASK]** Project Initialization & Blueprinting
* **[OBSERVATION/RESULT]** Defined the core architecture, strictly excluding RL in favor of Pymunk physics and grid-based stigmergy. Established the file structure and research variables.
* **[NEXT STEP]** Await user approval on the implementation plan, then begin Day 1 roadmap: initialize Pymunk physics engine and generate the arena walls and target shapes.

* **[TIMESTAMP]** 2026-06-03 18:07
* **[PHASE/TASK]** Base Architecture Implementation & Headless Testing
* **[OBSERVATION/RESULT]** Implemented the full Day 1-5 roadmap (`config`, `physics_engine`, `swarm_agents`, `stigmergy_grid`, `simulation_manager`, `data_logger`). Fixed a Pymunk `AssertionError` regarding shape/body addition order. Ran a headless baseline trial (10 agents, Circle shape). The swarm failed to push the shape through the gap within the 20s time limit, indicating a need for parameter tuning.
* **[NEXT STEP]** Build a Pygame Visualization module to observe the simulation dynamics in real-time, diagnose the pushing failures, and visualize the vector pheromone grid.

* **[TIMESTAMP]** 2026-06-03 18:10
